      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. The \"Noble Savage\" - portraying people of color as inherently noble or primitive, often romanticizing their lives in a simplistic way.\n2. The \"Sassy Black Woman\" - depicting Black women as overly loud, sassy, and aggressive, often to the point of being annoying.\n3. The \"Model Minority\" - suggesting people of Asian descent are universally successful, intelligent, and quiet, often ignoring their struggles and individuality.\n4. The \"Latino Gangster\" - portraying Latino men as dangerous, violent, and involved in crime, perpetuating the stereotype of the \"Latin Lover.\"\n5. The \"White Savior\" - depicting White characters as rescuers or heroes who save people of color from their own cultures or circumstances, reinforcing the idea that people of color need saving.",
