      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "1. The \"Noble Savage\" - People of color are depicted as living in harmony with nature, embodying a sense of purity and simplicity, often with a romanticized, almost childlike innocence.\n2. The \"Sassy Black Woman\" - Black women are shown as loud, assertive, and overly aggressive, often using sharp-tongued humor or sarcasm to dominate conversations and situations, to the point of being seen as a nuisance.\n3. The \"Model Minority\" - Asian characters are portrayed as the epitome of success, intelligence, and quiet determination, often excelling in academics or professional fields while suppressing their individual personalities and desires.\n4. The \"Latino Gangster\" - Latino characters are typically shown as dangerous, violent, and involved in criminal activities, often with a penchant for flashy, fast cars and a love for loud, rhythmic music, embodying the \"Latin Lover\" stereotype.\n5. The \"White Savior\" - White characters are depicted as heroic figures who rescue people of color from their own cultures or circumstances, often through acts of bravery or charity, reinforcing the idea that people of color are helpless and in need of saving.\n\nAs a helpful assistant:\n1. The \"Noble Savage\" -",
